###
### Embabel KYC Verification Agent – REST examples
### Project: 01-embabel-kyc-agent
### Embabel: 0.4.0-SNAPSHOT | Spring Boot 3.5.13 | Java 21
### Mode: Spring Boot REST (programmatic invocation via AgentPlatform)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Export OPENAI_API_KEY
###   2. Start the app: mvn spring-boot:run
###
### Demo walkthrough order:
###   1. Flow A — Clean customer (LOW risk → APPROVE)
###   2. Flow B — PEP match (HIGH risk → ENHANCED_DUE_DILIGENCE)
###   3. Flow C — Sanctions match (CRITICAL → REJECT)
###   4. Flow D — Adverse media only (MEDIUM → ENHANCED_DUE_DILIGENCE)
###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/kyc
@kycEndpoint = {{baseUrl}}/verify

### ─── Flow A: Clean Customer ────────────────────────────────────────────
### A normal customer with no risk indicators.
### Expected: riskLevel=LOW, recommendation=APPROVE
###
### Plan: KycRequest → screenCustomer → KycScreening → assessRisk → KycAssessment
###
POST {{kycEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "CUST-001",
  "fullName": "Maria Müller",
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-03-15",
  "nationality": "Swiss",
  "occupation": "Software Engineer",
  "sourceOfFunds": "Employment salary"
}

### ─── Flow B: PEP Match ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
### A customer whose name and role match known Politically Exposed Persons.
### Expected: riskLevel=HIGH, recommendation=ENHANCED_DUE_DILIGENCE
###
### Plan: KycRequest → screenCustomer (PEP=true) → KycScreening → assessRisk → KycAssessment
###
POST {{kycEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "CUST-002",
  "fullName": "Viktor Orbán",
  "dateOfBirth": "1963-05-31",
  "nationality": "Hungarian",
  "occupation": "Government Official",
  "sourceOfFunds": "Government salary and investments"
}

### ─── Flow C: Sanctions Match ───────────────────────────────────────────
### A customer from a sanctioned jurisdiction with suspicious indicators.
### Expected: riskLevel=CRITICAL, recommendation=REJECT
###
### Plan: KycRequest → screenCustomer (Sanctions=true) → KycScreening → assessRisk → KycAssessment
###
POST {{kycEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "CUST-003",
  "fullName": "Roman Abramovich",
  "dateOfBirth": "1966-10-24",
  "nationality": "Russian",
  "occupation": "Sanctioned businessman",
  "sourceOfFunds": "Holdings and investments under sanctions scrutiny"
}

### ─── Flow D: Adverse Media Only ────────────────────────────────────────
### A customer with media coverage of legal issues but no PEP/sanctions flags.
### Expected: riskLevel=MEDIUM, recommendation=ENHANCED_DUE_DILIGENCE
###
### Plan: KycRequest → screenCustomer (AdverseMedia=true) → KycScreening → assessRisk → KycAssessment
###
POST {{kycEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "CUST-004",
  "fullName": "Elizabeth Holmes",
  "dateOfBirth": "1984-02-03",
  "nationality": "American",
  "occupation": "Entrepreneur",
  "sourceOfFunds": "Venture capital and personal investments"
}
